14/07/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Local media Tuesday (13 July) quoted government spokesperson Saso Colakovski as saying talks on territorial decentralisation would continue this week.
Partners in the ruling coalition have not yet reached final consensus on all issues.
Further delay could affect the date of local elections in the fall.
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski concedes he has become less optimistic that a deal could be reached soon.
(MIA - 14/07/04)
